SUMMARY:Greenwood North - After Work Hike\, Intermediate
DESCRIPTION:GTA Hiking & Stuff\nOur first After Work hike of the season. T
 his will be a fast paced hike. We will hike at a moderate pace for 5 - 6 k
 m in 2 hrs or less. This hiking trail may still have some icy sections so 
 bring along your ice cleats just incase its more than expected. We should 
 be done before nightfall but a flashlight may be a good idea as well. Lets
  start getting in shape for summer.\n\nThe trail weaves through the forest
  and along a creek. There will be twists and turns and ups and downs but n
 othig serious. This event is about enjoying a hike at night.\n\n**Note**\n
 • Arrive on time! Don't let the group wait for you.\n• Know your limit
 s! Hike within it!\n• Dress for the conditions.\n• Free Parking\n• N
 o Dogs\n• The hike will be canceled if the weather doesn't cooperate.\n\
 n***Hike leaves promptly at 5:37 PM***\n\nHope to see you there!\n\n**LEGA
 L DISCLAIMER AND LIABILITY INFORMATION:**\n\nBy RSVP'ing and paying the ev
 ent fee (if applicable)\, you are confirming that you have read\, understa
 nd and accept the following:\n\n1. GTA Hiking Meetup is a private group. A
 ttending events is voluntary by you as a member. Participation in any acti
 vity with us is at your own risk.\n2. By joining this event as a member yo
 u agree to indemnify and hold harmless its organizers\, co-organizers\, as
 sistant organizers\, event hosts\, and other members from all claims or li
 ability of every type (including court costs and legal fees) for injury or
  death to any person or for damage to property\, loss of personal property
  or any other wrongful act arising out of or relating to your participatio
 n as a member. This agreement applies to you and to other persons (as your
  guests) who may accompany you in these endeavors.\n3. You also agree to h
 old the organizers as well as other group members harmless. By participati
 ng voluntarily in the group\, you expressly waive any and all such claims 
 against each and every other member in the group\, including without limit
 ation any and all claims against the group organizer\, co-organizers\, ass
 istant organizers\, and event hosts.
